How to enable and configure WASM SIMD acceleration in your Node.js or browser project using RuVector.

Node.js Setup

RuVector automatically uses native Rust bindings (napi-rs) in Node.js, which deliver better performance than WASM. SIMD is enabled at compile time:

```bash
npm install ruvector
# Native bindings are included for macOS (Apple Silicon + x86), Linux x86_64, Windows x86_64
```

The native bindings use AVX-512 on x86-64 and NEON on ARM64 automatically. No configuration is needed.

Browser / WASM Setup

```html
<!-- Import the WASM module -->
<script type="module">
  import init, { VectorDB } from '@ruvector/ruvector-wasm';

  // Initialize WASM (automatically uses SIMD128 if browser supports it)
  await init();

  const db = new VectorDB({ dimensions: 384, distanceMetric: 'Cosine' });
  await db.insert({ id: 'doc1', vector: Float32Array.from(embedding) });
  const results = await db.search({ vector: queryEmbedding, k: 10 });
</script>
```

Check SIMD support in browser:
```javascript
// Detect WASM SIMD128 support
const simdSupported = WebAssembly.validate(new Uint8Array([
  0x00, 0x61, 0x73, 0x6d, 0x01, 0x00, 0x00, 0x00,
